Finolex Industries Drops Most in 3 Years as Profit Declines 85%

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-05-02T12:20:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/finolex-industries-drops-most-in-3-years-as-profit-declines-85-.html
Finolex Industries Ltd. (FNXP) ,  India â€™s
biggest maker of plastic pipes, dropped the most in more than
three years in Mumbai trading after its fourth-quarter profit
declined 85 percent.  The shares fell 10.6 percent, the most since Jan. 22, 2008,
to 91.95 rupees at close of trading in Mumbai. The stock was the
worst performer on the BSE500 Index today.  Net income plunged to 87.8 million rupees ($2 million) in
the quarter ended March 31 from 597 million rupees a year
earlier. Sales rose 43 percent to 6.94 billion rupees, the
company said in a release to the Bombay Stock Exchange April 30.  To contact the reporter on this story:
